      <div type="book">
        <linkGrp type="notes"/>
        <div n="!W1808G1" type="letter"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-!W1808G1-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-!W1808G1-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-!W1808G1-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"><hi rend="underline">Sept</hi>. 12. 1735.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-!W1808G1-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-!W1808G1-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-!W1808G1-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">H</hi>Ere is a very ingenious observation upon the days of the week, and in rhyme, worth your observation, and very proper for the information of boys and girls, that they may not forget to reckon them.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-!W1808G1-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-!W1808G1-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-!W1808G1-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="verse-paragraph"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-!W1808G1-line-1"> Sunday's a pun-day,&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-!W1808G1-line-2"> Monday's a dun-day,</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-!W1808G1-line-3"> Tuesday's a news-day,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-!W1808G1-line-4"> Wednesday's a friend's-day,</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-!W1808G1-line-5"> Thursday's a curs'd-day,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-!W1808G1-line-6"> Friday's a dry-day,</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-!W1808G1-line-7"> Saturday's the latter-day.!W1808G1   </l></lg></div>
      </div>
